    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1882-04-28">April 28</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Couldn't you use this in Sunday's Press? Could you send me &#36;8.00 for it? Although
                printed four or five months ago in N. Y. Critic<ptr target="med.00654_n1"/>&#8212;I
                was thinking it might have the point now of <hi rend="italic">special
                    opportuneness</hi>&#8212;which is I suppose the main thing in
                paperdom&#8212;more than a freshly written piece.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
